      "description": "Comparison of CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) against published FDA pump experimental measurements across 5 operating points. RH < 1 at all conditions. The validation study incorporated a full UQ campaign (LHS, 500 samples, 12 parameters) whose aggregate sensitivity findings are documented in the body of this report; model-form uncertainty was bounded at ±8% NIH at 95% confidence."
